If you haven’t seen it, here are our suggestions for using CTRE swerve:

AdvantageKit 2024: Log Replay, Again! Programming
Unfortunately, CTRE’s swerve mechanism class is not designed in a way that makes it straightforward to adapt to an AdvantageKit project. This is because the hardware interaction is embedded in a library that cannot be easily customized to an IO layer structure. There are essentially two possible solutions: The entirety of the SwerveDrivetrain object can be placed inside an IO implementation.
